Sec. 59.028. APPRAISAL. (a) Before the board may loan money
for the purchase of land under this chapter, the board must have an
appraisal of the property made to determine its value.
(b) An appraiser representing the board must be qualified to
give competent appraisals of land. The board may use appraisers
employed by the board.
Added by Acts 1993, 73rd Leg., ch. 542, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1993.
Amended by Acts 1995, 74th Leg., ch. 1014, Sec. 17, eff. Jan. 1,
1996.

